					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I bought a toploader and have not been happy with it.  The RF only is a pain for me, but it sounds like it's not an issue for you.  The <span class="posthilit">vertical</span> lines are extremely noticeable, and hence I never play games on the toploader.  However, I do quite a bit of hardware hacking and the toploader is good for that because:
<br />1. It does not have a lockout chip on it, meaning neither do my games.
<br />2. You can put a EEPROM'd cart into it without having to tear the thing apart.  (actually I use a somewhat rare "game genie extender" for this).</div>

